        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 4:16PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 416 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 30
miles south of Ashland, or 38 miles northeast of Sheridan, moving
north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Birney.

This storm may produce flash flooding over the Remington burn scar
if it lingers for long. Be prepared to seek higher ground should a
warning be issued.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
